&gt;You seem to be confusing irritation and being offended. I am irritated of the crap liberals are forcing on everyone. Liberals are the ones getting offended by everything that they don't like.

It seems to be that when it's you it's irritation, when it's other people it's being offended. Irritated it literally a synonym for being offended:

&gt;resentful or annoyed, typically as a result of a perceived insult.  
&gt;  
&gt;"she sounded slightly offended"  
&gt;  
&gt;\*synonyms:\*upset, insulted, affronted, aggrieved, displeased, hurt, wounded, disgruntled, put out, annoyed, angry, cross, exasperated, indignant, **irritated**, piqued, vexed, irked, stung, galled, nettled, resentful, in a huff, huffy, in high dudgeon; More  
&gt;  
&gt;It's the usual typical liberal way. They play victim, then say that the person with the opposing opinion is being offended and is somehow being offensive at the same time. It's all play on emotion and empty arguments.

The person above literally did not say what you said they said, you just \*felt\* like that's what they were implying and thus went on a tirade about liberals getting offended, if that's not getting offended then I don't know what is.
